      <.faq_section>
        <.faq_item question="Is Wombie another social network?">
          No. Social networks optimise for time spent online. Wombie optimises for time spent in person. There's no feed, no follower counts, no algorithmic content.
        </.faq_item>
        <.faq_item question="How do I control who sees my events?">
          Every event has a visibility circle: Private (just you), Close Friends, Extended Circle, or Open. You set this when creating an event and can change it anytime.
        </.faq_item>
        <.faq_item question="Is it free?">
          Yes ‚Äî the core app is free. We'll add optional paid features for larger groups and organisations in future, but the personal social layer will always be free.
        </.faq_item>
        <.faq_item question="How is this different from a WhatsApp group?">
          Group chats are great for conversation. Wombie is for deciding and showing up. RSVP tracking, headcounts, and discovery from loose connections don't exist in a chat.
        </.faq_item>
        <.faq_item question="When is it available?">
          We're in private beta in Warsaw, Krakow, and Paris. Join the waitlist to get early access when we open your city.
        </.faq_item>
      </.faq_section>

